frameDefinitions: A System interacts with the environment (which may include a volitional agent) and goes into operation in accordance with its intended purpose.
Item-1 and Item-2 are compatible with each other if they can exist or function together in some context without problems, conflict, or other undesirable situation.
An Agent initiates the beginning of an ongoing Activity in which he will be continuously involved. '' 'At the same time, city-states began to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.'
A Self_mover intentionally moves in a Directionon a Path relative to landmark that is neither the Source nor the Goal of the overall motion.
This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
A Cause triggers a System to operate in accordance with its intended purpose.
frameExamples: The alarm <t>went off</t> as she walked through the entrance.
Make sure your site is <t>compatible</t> with any browser.
At the same time, city-states <t>began</t> to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.
Ambrose Powell <t>forded</t> over on one horse, and we drove the others after him.
Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
Smoking a cigarette will normally not <t>set off</t> a smoke alarm.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>System</fen> interacts with the environment and activates.
The time when the <fen>System</fen> triggers.
Where the <fen>System</fen> goes off.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_1</fen> marks the grammatically more prominent of the two entities, i.e.the subject in active clauses, when they are expressed separately.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_2</fen> marks the grammatically less prominent of the <fen>Items</fen> when they are expressed separately.
This role is used when the <fen>Items</fen> are expressed jointly in a phrase, either a plural or a coordinated NP.
This Frame Element is used for expressions that indicate a <fen>Parameter</fen> or respect in which the <fen>Items</fen> are said to be compatible, not in conflict.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> starts.
This role identifies the being that starts the intentional <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This is a sentient being or a vehicle steered by a sentient being which moves.
Any expression which implies a definite starting-point of motion expresses the frame element <fen>Source</fen>.
Any description of a trajectory of motion which is neither a <fen>Source</fen> nor a <fen>Goal</fen> expresses the frame element <fen>Path</fen>, excluding directional expressions:
Any expression which indicates where the <fen>Self_mover</fen> ends up as a result of the motion expresses the frame element <fen>Goal</fen>.
The configuration formed by the entire <fen>Path</fen> of the <fen>Self_mover</fen>, taken simultaneously.
The direction in which the <fen>Self_mover</fen> goes.
The time at which the motion takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the motion (which is specified by a <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) is located.
The <fen>Kindler</fen> is the person performing the intentional act.
The <fen>Flame</fen> is what is created by the Kindler.
The Flamables is the the object that is set on fire by the Kindler.
The cause of the fire.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event takes place.
The <fen>Cause</fen> interacts with the <fen>System</fen> such that conditions are met for the <fen>System</fen> to operate.
The <fen>System</fen> interacts with or detects the <fen>Cause</fen> and activates.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
The time when the triggering takes place.
Where the triggering takes place.
